### 2. Login
# @name login
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### 3. Get Appointments (Requires Auth)
GET {{host}}/api/appointments
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}
# Note: Since we are using Cookie Identity by default in .NET Identity, this might return 401 if we don't handle cookies.
# However, for API we usually want JWT. The current setup uses default Identity cookies. 
# We'll need to check if we enabled JWT or if we rely on cookies.
# Assuming Cookies for now, standard .NET Identity behavior.
# In VS Code REST Client, cookies are usually handled automatically if configured, but let's see.

